==English==

===Etymology===
From {{etyl|fro|en}} {{m|fro|augmentacion}}, from {{etyl|la|en}} {{m|la|augmentatio}}, verbal noun from {{m|la|augmento||to increase}}

===Pronunciation===
* {{rhymes|en|eɪʃən}}

===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# The act or process of [[augment]]ing.
# {{lb|en|heraldry}} A particular [[mark of honour]], granted by the [[sovereign]] in consideration of some [[noble]] action, or by [[favour]]; and either [[quarter]]ed with the [[family arms]], or on an [[escutcheon]] or [[canton]].
# {{lb|en|medicine}} A [[surgical]] procedure to enlarge a body part, as [[breast augmentation]].
# {{lb|en|medicine}} The stage of a [[disease]] during which [[symptom]]s increase or continue.
# {{lb|en|music}} A [[compositional]] technique where the composer lengthens the [[melody]] by lengthening its [[note value]]s.
# {{lb|en|Scotland|law}} An increase of stipend obtained by a parish minister by an action raised in the Court of Teinds against the titular and heritors.

